chapter Power Sets
Define the power set of a set - the set of all its subsets.

axiom Axiom of Power Set
conclusion ∃ Z ∀ Y ↔ ∈ Y Z ⊆ Y X
distinct-variables (Z Y X, Y Z X)

theorem Power Sets Are Unique
prove ∃ Z ∀ Y ↔ ∈ Y Z ⊆ Y X
prove ∃! Z ∀ Y ↔ ∈ Y Z ⊆ Y X
qed

term powerSet (X) format (𝒫X) (∀ Y ↔ ∈ Y _ ⊆ Y X)

theorem Subset Is in Power Set
premise ⊆ Y X
prove ∀ Y ↔ ∈ Y powerSet X ⊆ Y X
prove ↔ ∈ Y powerSet X ⊆ Y X
prove ∈ Y powerSet X
qed

theorem Element of Power Set Is Subset
premise ∈ Y powerSet X
prove ∀ Y ↔ ∈ Y powerSet X ⊆ Y X
prove ↔ ∈ Y powerSet X ⊆ Y X
prove ⊆ Y X
qed

theorem ∅ Is in Any Power Set
prove ⊆ ∅ X
prove ∈ ∅ powerSet X
qed

theorem Any Set Is in Its Own Power Set
prove ⊆ X X
prove ∈ X powerSet X
qed
